- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as constituency parsing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the benefits of pre-training and fine-tuning models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing models that can perform language-related tasks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural network models for pre-training and fine-tuning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not deal with visual data, but it is still possible as the paper uses self-attention mechanisms which are commonly used in computer vision tasks.
